    "connections_to_other_philosophers": {
      "influence": "Epicurus was heavily influenced by Democritus's atomism, adopting and modifying his theory of the universe. He also drew inspiration from the Cyrenaics' emphasis on pleasure, but refined their concept to focus on the absence of pain.",
      "contrast": "Epicurus's philosophy stands in stark contrast to Stoicism, which emphasized virtue and duty as the highest goods, and viewed pleasure with suspicion. He also differed from Plato and Aristotle, who placed greater emphasis on reason and intellectual contemplation as paths to the good life."
    },
